com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum

Class AbstractStringnumMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum.AbstractStringnumMap<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NonNullValueStringnumMap, StringnumMap

    public abstract class AbstractStringnumMap<V>
extends Object
implements Map<String,V>
    A lightweight map from String to anything. It uses a Stringnum internally, and supports reuse of the Stringnum in multiple maps. The performance, when accessing with non-hacked Strings depends on the concrete Stringnum implementation. Note that the data array size is proportional to the Stringum size. It is NOT thread-safe.
